Key Match Events: Jayson Tatum's 33-point performance led the Celtics to a 118-115 win over the Timberwolves, and Anthony Edwards' 3-pointer fell short at the buzzer, ending the Timberwolves' chance to send the game into overtime.
Post-Match Reflections: Jayson Tatum's big night lifts short-handed Celtics past Timberwolves 118-115
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Celtics committed just four turnovers while the Timberwolves turned it over 16 times on the night.
Others: Julius Randle led Minnesota with 27 points, eight rebounds and seven assists, while Naz Reid added 20 points off the bench, and Jaden McDaniels had 19 points and eight boards.
